cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper proposes a method for unsupervised domain adaptation in computer vision tasks, which involves learning a target-specific feature extraction module using a trained source model without accessing the source data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also mentions self-supervised pseudo-labeling, which is a common technique in natural language processing tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the experiments involve image datasets, suggesting a potential connection to cs.MM (Multimedia).
